div.p:
For God is much more Honoured by our Publick Addresses to him than he can be, by any thing we can do in Private; not but we may and ought to use Private Prayers suitable to our necessities, but we must not neglect his Publick Worship, which the Private ought not to hinder, but promote;

because in Truth,

                  See more at large in a late Discourse of the daily and Publick Prayers, by the Reverend Dean of Peterborough. it is defective without Publick, being only Worship, but not so properly Honour, Glory, Sacrifice and Service.
